1
00:00:00,050 --> 00:00:00,940
Will you marry me?

2
00:00:01,910 --> 00:00:03,539
How could you joke about a proposal?

3
00:00:03,760 --> 00:00:06,023
I’ll get the surgery while Khao is still mad at me.

4
00:00:06,152 --> 00:00:07,337
What if you die?

5
00:00:07,496 --> 00:00:09,137
You won’t get to say goodbye to Khao.

6
00:00:09,491 --> 00:00:10,414
Can you help me with drawing?

7
00:00:11,028 --> 00:00:14,379
Didn’t you tell me earlier that you didn’t need my help?

8
00:00:15,260 --> 00:00:18,765
If you have anything I can help, let me know.

9
00:00:19,542 --> 00:00:20,597
Didn’t you say that?

10
00:00:21,392 --> 00:00:23,068
This is for you.

11
00:00:24,845 --> 00:00:26,204
How is it? Does it look good?

12
00:00:26,773 --> 00:00:29,853
(This kind of moment, it happens again.)

13
00:00:35,600 --> 00:00:38,130
A television drama adaptation from the original Chinese novel A Love So Beautiful written by Zhao Qianqian

14
00:01:44,303 --> 00:01:45,330
You didn’t get enough sleep?

15
00:01:45,920 --> 00:01:47,108
You have bags under your eyes.

16
00:01:49,924 --> 00:01:51,970
How ungrateful of you!

17
00:01:52,032 --> 00:01:55,117
I stayed up drawing for you all night and you have the nerve to ask about my eyebags?

18
00:01:56,613 --> 00:01:57,909
You need me to get on my knees with gratitude or what?

19
00:01:59,263 --> 00:02:01,106
Hey, where are you taking my notebook?

20
00:02:01,336 --> 00:02:03,349
What? You gave it to me, didn’t you?

21
00:02:04,460 --> 00:02:05,111
I…

22
00:02:13,151 --> 00:02:14,417
Som. Som.

23
00:02:17,151 --> 00:02:18,425
Where have you been?

24
00:02:18,740 --> 00:02:20,825
I’ve been calling you and you didn’t pick up the phone.

25
00:02:22,440 --> 00:02:24,768
Oh, Im, this is Chadjen.

26
00:02:25,047 --> 00:02:26,613
Chad, this is Im, a friend of mine.

27
00:02:30,690 --> 00:02:31,500
I see.

28
00:02:33,917 --> 00:02:34,709
Chadjen.

29
00:02:35,475 --> 00:02:36,250
Som-O.

30
00:02:37,351 --> 00:02:41,586
And is Chadjen your… what now?

31
00:02:41,856 --> 00:02:42,512
Friend.

32
00:02:43,688 --> 00:02:44,534
He’s a friend.

33
00:02:45,696 --> 00:02:46,416
We’re friends…

34
00:02:47,371 --> 00:02:48,459
What do you study, Chad?

35
00:02:49,407 --> 00:02:50,308
Medicine.

36
00:02:51,168 --> 00:02:52,979
Chad is actually a second year.

37
00:02:55,025 --> 00:02:57,980
Oh, hello, Chadjen.

38
00:02:58,669 --> 00:03:00,342
Sorry I called you by your nickname just now.

39
00:03:00,779 --> 00:03:01,562
It’s no big deal.

40
00:03:02,502 --> 00:03:03,106
Som.

41
00:03:03,804 --> 00:03:05,339
Your…your name tag.

42
00:03:06,948 --> 00:03:08,788
The tag! The tag…

43
00:03:09,718 --> 00:03:11,010
I think I forgot to bring it.

44
00:03:13,717 --> 00:03:14,817
No.

45
00:03:15,414 --> 00:03:18,145
If you don’t have it, the upperclassmen are going to go ballistic.

46
00:03:18,743 --> 00:03:20,165
Let’s go back and grab it.

47
00:03:20,186 --> 00:03:21,222
No way!

48
00:03:21,303 --> 00:03:22,094
I’m not going back.

49
00:03:23,062 --> 00:03:24,219
It’s just a name tag.

50
00:03:25,678 --> 00:03:27,801
Are you taking me back to the hazing?

51
00:03:28,158 --> 00:03:29,857
Of course.

52
00:03:30,675 --> 00:03:34,103
If you don’t show up, they’re going to punish the rest of us.

53
00:03:36,299 --> 00:03:37,509
This is ridiculous, Im.

54
00:03:38,102 --> 00:03:39,663
They should punish me if I don’t go.

55
00:03:39,680 --> 00:03:41,560
Why would they punish everyone else just to make me feel bad?

56
00:03:42,041 --> 00:03:43,528
No, I’m not going.

57
00:03:43,573 --> 00:03:44,682
But, Som-O—

58
00:03:44,694 --> 00:03:45,848
I’m not going!

59
00:03:47,413 --> 00:03:48,456
You don’t have to go, either.

60
00:03:48,645 --> 00:03:50,281
This could end very easily if everyone just didn’t participate.

61
00:03:51,226 --> 00:03:52,619
No, you can’t.

62
00:03:52,865 --> 00:03:54,020
You have to go.

63
00:03:54,817 --> 00:03:55,712
Please, Som.

64
00:03:56,389 --> 00:03:57,462
Just go!

65
00:03:58,124 --> 00:03:58,931
Come with me.

66
00:03:59,152 --> 00:04:01,260
Please, Som-O!

67
00:04:02,176 --> 00:04:03,829
Som, come with me.

68
00:04:05,004 --> 00:04:06,213
Please.

69
00:04:12,776 --> 00:04:13,808
Fine.

70
00:04:14,767 --> 00:04:15,721
Whatever.

71
00:04:25,668 --> 00:04:26,637
Don’t even say anything.

72
00:04:27,345 --> 00:04:28,207
I didn’t.

73
00:04:29,368 --> 00:04:32,237
Why did you pull my pants, though?

74
00:04:38,536 --> 00:04:39,703
Why did you cough, then?

75
00:04:48,034 --> 00:04:48,714
You alright?

76
00:04:49,602 --> 00:04:50,565
Yes, Dad.

77
00:04:53,856 --> 00:04:54,413
Oh.

78
00:04:54,583 --> 00:04:55,210
Hello.

79
00:04:55,256 --> 00:04:56,317
Hi.

80
00:04:56,340 --> 00:04:57,432
Good thing you’re here.

81
00:04:57,589 --> 00:04:59,299
New, stay with Chad for now.

82
00:04:59,466 --> 00:05:01,408
I’ll be handling the document.

83
00:05:02,374 --> 00:05:03,103
Alright.

84
00:05:07,077 --> 00:05:07,862
You ready?

85
00:05:09,260 --> 00:05:10,503
I have to be even if I’m not, don’t I?

86
00:05:13,143 --> 00:05:14,671
Did you tell Khao?

87
00:05:20,398 --> 00:05:24,013
Are you sure you’re not going to tell her?

88
00:05:26,613 --> 00:05:27,774
Please, Chad.

89
00:05:29,499 --> 00:05:30,767
Don’t tell her.

90
00:05:34,982 --> 00:05:35,614
Alright.

91
00:05:39,082 --> 00:05:40,517
I’ll do what you ask.

92
00:05:51,760 --> 00:05:52,706
Don’t be afraid, Dad.

93
00:05:54,626 --> 00:05:55,669
Of course I’m not.

94
00:06:04,635 --> 00:06:05,211
Right.

95
00:06:08,257 --> 00:06:09,413
I’ll be strong.

96
00:06:11,965 --> 00:06:13,309
I’ll be right back.

97
00:06:29,927 --> 00:06:33,908
As I’ve discussed with you, we’re making this patient a case study,

98
00:06:33,971 --> 00:06:37,515
so I’ve brought some medical students with me.

99
00:06:38,485 --> 00:06:39,111
Of course.

100
00:06:39,423 --> 00:06:40,306
Please.

101
00:06:46,160 --> 00:06:46,823
Excuse me.

102
00:06:47,600 --> 00:06:50,657
Professor, here’s the test result you asked for.

103
00:06:51,350 --> 00:06:52,706
They asked me to give it to you.

104
00:06:54,866 --> 00:06:55,438
Oh?

105
00:07:04,751 --> 00:07:06,208
Do you know him?

106
00:07:07,420 --> 00:07:08,414
He’s an underclassman of mine.

107
00:07:10,020 --> 00:07:10,857
Get well soon.

108
00:07:11,374 --> 00:07:12,114
Don’t worry.

109
00:07:14,740 --> 00:07:16,394
Excuse me.

110
00:07:17,201 --> 00:07:17,782
Goodbye.

111
00:07:17,994 --> 00:07:18,660
Bye.

112
00:07:20,884 --> 00:07:24,042
Som-O, please come to the hazing today.

113
00:07:25,727 --> 00:07:26,365
Please.

114
00:07:27,365 --> 00:07:28,315
I beg.

115
00:07:28,872 --> 00:07:29,928
Do it for the rest of us.

116
00:07:30,477 --> 00:07:31,425
Please, Som-O.

117
00:07:32,232 --> 00:07:33,862
- Please. - I haven't said anything.

118
00:07:35,121 --> 00:07:35,709
Please?

119
00:07:36,321 --> 00:07:38,010
Fine. I’ll show up.

120
00:07:38,730 --> 00:07:39,509
Really?

121
00:07:40,854 --> 00:07:41,428
Yeah.

122
00:07:41,598 --> 00:07:42,866
Can I get a hug?

123
00:07:43,561 --> 00:07:44,188
Sure.

124
00:07:44,974 --> 00:07:46,508
Yeah!

125
00:07:50,819 --> 00:07:52,171
Good job not being late today!

126
00:07:52,368 --> 00:07:53,684
Give yourself a round of applause.

127
00:08:01,457 --> 00:08:02,702
Where is your name tag?

128
00:08:03,284 --> 00:08:04,817
Where is your name tag?

129
00:08:05,171 --> 00:08:06,626
Where is your name tag?

130
00:08:07,026 --> 00:08:08,134
I forgot it.

131
00:08:10,497 --> 00:08:11,223
Hurry up!

132
00:08:12,161 --> 00:08:13,620
Go, go, go!

133
00:08:13,665 --> 00:08:14,804
Hurry up.

134
00:08:14,831 --> 00:08:16,047
Keep going.

135
00:08:16,080 --> 00:08:17,528
Quickly!

136
00:08:20,510 --> 00:08:21,709
Faster!

137
00:08:23,688 --> 00:08:25,731
Fasten your pace, you there!

138
00:08:27,360 --> 00:08:28,531
Get up there!

139
00:08:28,545 --> 00:08:29,444
Run.

140
00:08:30,337 --> 00:08:32,822
See? Nothing good about showing up.

141
00:08:33,284 --> 00:08:35,321
At least they didn't make us sing today.

142
00:08:35,908 --> 00:08:37,120
You jinx.

143
00:08:37,392 --> 00:08:38,728
Did you just call your friend a jinx?

144
00:08:39,173 --> 00:08:41,007
Five more rounds for all of you.

145
00:08:42,475 --> 00:08:43,971
When does this stop, Im?

146
00:08:46,447 --> 00:08:47,379
The hazing?

147
00:08:47,533 --> 00:08:50,008
I think it goes on until the upperclassmen are happy.

148
00:08:51,986 --> 00:08:53,460
Win them over, you mean?

149
00:08:55,878 --> 00:08:57,266
Like, everyone’s disciplined,

150
00:08:58,505 --> 00:08:59,831
everyone shows up,

151
00:09:00,906 --> 00:09:03,242
and just follows orders.

152
00:09:04,877 --> 00:09:06,312
Is there no other way?

153
00:09:11,878 --> 00:09:13,822
Are you ready for surgery?

154
00:09:14,186 --> 00:09:14,814
Yes.

155
00:09:17,908 --> 00:09:18,808
Hold on, Doctor.

156
00:09:34,891 --> 00:09:35,571
Dad.

157
00:09:47,025 --> 00:09:47,903
Hair band?

158
00:09:49,090 --> 00:09:50,075
Does it belong to Khao?

159
00:09:52,228 --> 00:09:52,817
Yes.

160
00:09:55,360 --> 00:09:59,074
Can you give it to her when you can?

161
00:10:09,520 --> 00:10:11,072
You have to be the one to give it back to her.

162
00:10:12,000 --> 00:10:13,205
I won’t do it for you.

163
00:10:15,352 --> 00:10:16,109
Dad.

164
00:10:17,708 --> 00:10:19,217
Please give it back to her.

165
00:10:27,382 --> 00:10:28,063
Alright.

166
00:10:28,308 --> 00:10:29,186
I promise.

167
00:10:30,145 --> 00:10:31,420
I’ll give it back to her.

168
00:10:33,198 --> 00:10:34,210
Thank you.

169
00:10:36,197 --> 00:10:38,068
I hope she doesn’t lash out at you.

170
00:10:42,490 --> 00:10:43,308
You stubborn boy.

171
00:10:52,645 --> 00:10:53,423
I’m ready now.

172
00:11:22,758 --> 00:11:24,477
I love you, New.

173
00:11:39,262 --> 00:11:40,001
Chadjen!

174
00:11:40,140 --> 00:11:40,708
Chad!

175
00:11:41,410 --> 00:11:42,191
Chadjen!

176
00:11:42,349 --> 00:11:45,819
Chadjen, how could you keep this from me?

177
00:11:45,958 --> 00:11:47,708
New is getting surgery!

178
00:11:48,165 --> 00:11:49,682
What were you thinking?

179
00:11:50,091 --> 00:11:52,185
Khao told me over the phone just now and I rushed here.

180
00:11:52,327 --> 00:11:53,706
Good thing the hazing was over early today.

181
00:11:54,440 --> 00:11:55,118
What?

182
00:11:55,616 --> 00:11:56,711
Khao knows this, too?

183
00:11:57,887 --> 00:11:59,139
No thanks to you!

184
00:12:01,389 --> 00:12:03,259
Why did you keep it a secret?

185
00:12:04,770 --> 00:12:07,235
You should know there is no such thing as secrets.

186
00:12:10,973 --> 00:12:12,653
Oh, I don’t mean to offend you, Uncle.

187
00:12:14,854 --> 00:12:15,524
It’s alright.

188
00:12:15,751 --> 00:12:16,551
I understand.

189
00:12:33,910 --> 00:12:36,979
Chadjen, you...

190
00:12:40,635 --> 00:12:41,817
I promised New I wouldn’t.

191
00:12:48,968 --> 00:12:51,771
I don’t know what this means.

192
00:12:53,020 --> 00:12:58,337
But New wants you to have this, Khao.

193
00:13:22,028 --> 00:13:24,503
Hey, don’t worry.

194
00:13:25,965 --> 00:13:29,506
The surgeon who’s operating on New is very good.

195
00:13:31,718 --> 00:13:32,915
No matter how good she is,

196
00:13:33,548 --> 00:13:35,376
there’s still a chance that something might go wrong, right?

197
00:13:38,717 --> 00:13:41,405
Yes, but it’s not likely.

198
00:13:43,597 --> 00:13:47,801
Do you guys think New would forgive me?

199
00:13:50,394 --> 00:13:52,208
He’s the one who needs forgiving.

200
00:13:52,903 --> 00:13:53,909
What did you even do, Khao?

201
00:14:01,700 --> 00:14:03,000
Will you please talk to me?

202
00:14:13,770 --> 00:14:14,626
What are you doing?

203
00:14:18,814 --> 00:14:21,220
Khao, you are pretty and cool.

204
00:14:25,602 --> 00:14:26,579
Will you marry me?

205
00:14:31,657 --> 00:14:33,405
How could you joke about a proposal?

206
00:14:40,167 --> 00:14:41,957
I always lash out at him.

207
00:14:44,198 --> 00:14:48,616
I lashed out at him about this hair band, too.

208
00:14:51,271 --> 00:14:53,937
He’s always treated everything as a joke.

209
00:14:55,244 --> 00:14:57,408
But life is no joke.

210
00:15:00,982 --> 00:15:03,595
Our time is very precious.

211
00:15:06,317 --> 00:15:09,010
And I don’t even know how much time I have left.

212
00:15:11,256 --> 00:15:12,411
And now he…

213
00:15:13,451 --> 00:15:14,102
New is…

214
00:15:14,920 --> 00:15:17,602
Now he’s…

215
00:15:38,982 --> 00:15:39,705
Khao…

216
00:15:53,554 --> 00:15:54,536
Take it easy.

217
00:15:59,094 --> 00:16:00,506
I can’t do this.

218
00:16:07,850 --> 00:16:09,007
You got this.

219
00:16:10,219 --> 00:16:11,309
Don’t worry, Khao.

220
00:16:13,066 --> 00:16:14,629
New will be here soon.

221
00:16:19,106 --> 00:16:20,198
He will.

222
00:16:48,764 --> 00:16:49,411
New!

223
00:16:52,925 --> 00:16:53,847
- New! - New.

224
00:16:54,040 --> 00:16:55,411
Oh, hello, Chadjen.

225
00:16:56,340 --> 00:16:56,798
New.

226
00:16:56,805 --> 00:16:57,537
Hello.

227
00:16:58,309 --> 00:17:00,034
He’s a friend of mine.

228
00:17:00,837 --> 00:17:02,287
Oh, I see.

229
00:17:02,672 --> 00:17:04,139
Well, good news.

230
00:17:04,303 --> 00:17:06,139
The surgery was a success.

231
00:17:06,235 --> 00:17:07,677
The patient made it safe and sound.

232
00:17:08,112 --> 00:17:10,136
He’ll wake up from the anesthetics soon enough.

233
00:17:10,862 --> 00:17:13,657
I’ll leave your friend in your care, Chadjen.

234
00:17:14,832 --> 00:17:15,505
Of course.

235
00:17:17,441 --> 00:17:18,666
Thank you, Professor.

236
00:17:28,195 --> 00:17:32,379
How are you doing with the case study the Professor asked you to see?

237
00:17:32,940 --> 00:17:34,808
I’m still studying.

238
00:17:34,868 --> 00:17:39,210
But I think I’ll understand in a few weeks.

239
00:17:39,718 --> 00:17:40,337
Good job.

240
00:17:40,349 --> 00:17:41,111
Thanks.

241
00:17:43,505 --> 00:17:44,225
Are you alright?

242
00:17:45,241 --> 00:17:46,016
I’m sorry.

243
00:17:49,056 --> 00:17:50,109
Oh, Chadjen.

244
00:17:50,592 --> 00:17:51,419
Im.

245
00:17:51,435 --> 00:17:53,139
Hello, Chadjen.

246
00:17:53,958 --> 00:17:54,745
Yeah, hi.

247
00:17:54,767 --> 00:17:56,779
Im, this is Chad.

248
00:17:57,300 --> 00:17:58,517
You don’t have to be so respectful.

249
00:17:58,810 --> 00:18:00,305
He’s a second year student, just like you.

250
00:18:01,671 --> 00:18:03,497
This is Im, my sister.

251
00:18:03,958 --> 00:18:05,607
She’s here to have her leg checked up.

252
00:18:05,814 --> 00:18:09,000
She’s been made to take a jog around the building for days.

253
00:18:14,505 --> 00:18:16,337
You…

254
00:18:18,105 --> 00:18:19,066
I’ll call you later.

255
00:18:23,706 --> 00:18:24,336
What?

256
00:18:29,570 --> 00:18:32,475
Hey, don’t you tell anyone that I’m—

257
00:18:32,494 --> 00:18:33,220
You’re an imposter.

258
00:18:34,430 --> 00:18:35,059
Shh!

259
00:18:35,097 --> 00:18:35,808
Am I right?

260
00:18:37,008 --> 00:18:37,899
Not so loud.

261
00:18:38,090 --> 00:18:40,505
If the upperclassmen know, they’re going to give me an earful.

262
00:18:40,960 --> 00:18:45,711
More importantly, do not tell Som-O, at all costs.

263
00:18:47,517 --> 00:18:49,668
You want me to just do nothing?

264
00:18:57,634 --> 00:18:58,364
Will you?

265
00:19:02,442 --> 00:19:03,136
Please.

266
00:19:05,161 --> 00:19:06,158
Please, Chadjen.

267
00:19:07,294 --> 00:19:08,201
Please, please, please.

268
00:19:08,231 --> 00:19:08,897
Please.

269
00:19:09,294 --> 00:19:09,891
Please.

270
00:19:10,343 --> 00:19:10,962
Please.

271
00:19:11,802 --> 00:19:12,429
Fine.

272
00:19:14,982 --> 00:19:16,776
But you have to help me with something.

273
00:19:19,548 --> 00:19:20,321
Help you?

274
00:19:21,964 --> 00:19:22,607
With what?

275
00:19:39,281 --> 00:19:40,782
Has New come to, Uncle?

276
00:19:41,936 --> 00:19:42,782
So far, no.

277
00:19:43,500 --> 00:19:48,405
Would you mind keeping him company for a bit, Khao?

278
00:19:48,940 --> 00:19:50,114
I’ll go get something to eat.

279
00:19:50,903 --> 00:19:51,665
Do you want anything?

280
00:19:51,908 --> 00:19:53,198
No, thank you.

281
00:20:01,807 --> 00:20:02,614
Khao.

282
00:20:04,245 --> 00:20:06,305
I think New would be really happy

283
00:20:06,644 --> 00:20:09,293
if you’re the first person he sees when he opens his eyes.

284
00:20:25,917 --> 00:20:27,213
